Getting critial alerts on cpu:
  When update-apt-xapi is running, CPU usage stays at 100%
  See 
  http://askubuntu.com/questions/79481/is-100-cpu-usage-harmful-while-update-apt-xapi-runs
  http://sapnwnewbie.blogspot.co.uk/2010/11/high-cpu-usage-by-update-apt-xapi.html

  I put a fix in both the daily and weekly cron job:
  
  /etc/cron.daily/apt:
  line 462: nice -n 19 ionice -c3 update-apt-xapian-index --update -q -u
                 ^^^NEW                                 ^^^NEW

  /etc/cron.weekly/apt-xapian-index:
  # Rebuild the index
  if [ -x "$CMD" ]
  then
          if [ -x "$IONICE" ]
          then
                  nice -n 19 $IONICE -c 3 $CMD --update --quiet
          else                                  ^^^NEW
                  nice -n 19 $CMD --quiet
          fi
  fi
  
